com.isti.traceview.common
Interface IEvent

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractEvent, Arrival, DefaultEvent, Earthquake, Pick, QCIssue, StateOfHealth
public interface IEvent
extends Comparable

This base interface represents event, i.e some occasion with time and duration which can be plotted on channel's graph. Event here is as an abstract object that is defined by a start time, duration, and series of other parameters and needs to be displayed in the channel panels. Event has set of parameter-value pairs, so every type of event can be processed in the same manner. This interface extends "Comparable" in order to define events sorting order. Note that we use the word "Event" in a software sense, not seismological.

Author:
Max Kokoulin
